main event: An observer in Walker, Minnesota saw a yellowish star-like object in the sky on February 6, 1968, for about 30 minutes.
interesting points: The object appeared to be standing still initially but seemed to move higher in the sky over time., The object was described as translucent and larger than the stars around it., The observer noted that no sound was heard during the sighting., The object vanished suddenly after being observed for about 15 seconds near the end of the sighting., The report also includes a letter from a member of Congress forwarding the sighting report to the Department of the Air Force.
witness description: A 39-year-old female stenographer reported the sighting; she was accompanied by a friend.
